If people leech this I will Delete it. Also, this is somewhat Anti-Noob.. There are no errors. I just made it hard to find stuff in some parts.

[b]Purpose: [/b][i]To Create a webclient[/i]

[b]Difficulty: [/b][i]6/10[/i]

[b]Assumed Knowledge: [/b][i]Java Fundamentals?[/i]

[b]Client Base: [/b][i]All[/i]

[b]Classes Modified: [/b][i]Client.java, Class 30 Sub 2 Sub 1 Sub 1[/i]


[b][u]Procedure[/u][/b]

[center]Client.java[/center]
[b]Step 1: [/b][i]Go into your client folder and open up client.java. Search for [code]void int()[/code]. Once there repalce the whole void with this [code]public final void init()
	{
		try
		{
			anInt957 = 0;
			anInt958 = 0;
			method52(true);
			aBoolean959 = true;
			signlink.storeid = 32;
			signlink.startpriv(InetAddress.getLocalHost());
			setserver("");
			method2(503, false, 765);
		}
		catch (Exception exception)
		{
			return;
		}
	}[/code]
[b]Step 2: [/b][i]Search for [code]private final void method28[/code] Once you have found it replace the whole thing with [code]private final void method28(String s)
    {
        System.out.println(s);
    }
[/code] 

[b]Step 3: [/b][i]Search for [code]public final URL getCodeBase()[/code] Replace the whole thing with [code]public final URL getCodeBase(){
        try
       {
                return new URL("http://"+server+":" + (80 + anInt958));
       }
        catch(Exception _ex) { }
        return super.getCodeBase();
    }
[/code]

[b]Step 4: [/b][i]Search for [code]public static void setserver[/code] And Replace it with [code]public static void setserver(String s)
	{
		server = s;
	}
[/code]

[b]Step 5: [/b][i] Find [code]setserver(args[0],args[1],args[2]);[/code] And replace it with [code]setserver(args[0]);
[/code]

[center]Other[/center]

[b]Step 1: [/b][i]Open up Class 30 sub 2 sub 1 sub 1 and import this package [code]java.net.URL;[/code]

[b]Step 2: [/b][i]Find where your picture loads from. Make it look like this [code]Image image = Toolkit.getDefaultToolkit().getImage(new URL("WEBSITEWHEREPCILOADSFROM"));[/code] Upload a picture, 766X503, to a website and place the link to the picture "WEBSITEWHEREPCILOADSFROM" There.

[b]Step 3: [/b][i] Open up your META-INF Folder and delete everything. Make a .txt file in the META-INF Folder and place this inside of it [code]Manifest-Version: 1.0
Created-By: 1.5.0_04 (Sun Microsystems Inc.)
Main-Class: client
[/code]
Then Click File -> Save as -> MANIFEST.MF -> All Files.

[b]Step 4: [/b][i] Make your client load the cache from Mopars. Follow my Making a JAR And Signing a JAR Tutorial(Will be made later)

[b]Step 5: [/b][i] Upload the JAR to your webpage. Make a file called index.html and place this in it [code] <html>
<title>Servername Webclient</title>
<center><applet code="client"      
archive="WHEREYOURJARISAT"
width="766" height="503">
<param name=foo value="bar">
</applet>
</html>
[/code]
If everything has been completed right you now have a working webclient that connects to servers!

